        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 17 at 5:08PM CDT by NWS Springfield MO</headline>
        <description>At 508 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sparta, or near Ozark. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ozark, Sparta, and Linden.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
